cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use Proteus or refer to the plasticity-substrate architecture in academic work, please cite this repository."
title: "Proteus — Plasticity Substrate for Frozen-Weight LLMs"
abstract: >-
  A three-loop architecture giving frozen-weight LLMs online state adaptation
  under deterministic governance. Loop A applies a banded controller over
  pre-sampling entropy (challenge) and Adaptive Conformal Inference band width
  (skill) to steer retrieval depth, control-vector gain, and scaffold density
  toward the Csikszentmihalyi flow condition. Loop B records every state
  transition to an Ed25519-signed, SHA-256-linked SQLite chain. Loop C performs
  approval-gated consolidation via canary-tested control vectors and LoRA
  adapters. Proposed as Road VI (Plasticity Substrate) in the Five Preverbal
  Roads framework. Released with cryptographically committed,
  hostile-reviewed benchmark (proteus-bench v1.0.1, PROTEUS-002).
type: software
